$ Oracle wait event: cursor: pin S wait on X
@ cursor: pin S wait on X

? *cursor: pin S wait on X* occurs in the context of *SQL statement parsing* and indicates that a session waits requested aa shared mutex pin and another session is holding an exclusive mutex pin on the same *cursor object*.

This event is caused by one (or more?) of
  • Under sized shared pool (should not be an issued with Automatic Memory Management)
  • High frequency of *hard parses*
  • High SQL statement version count
  • Bugs
  • Parse errors (see KB149113)
  

